        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 2:08PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 208 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ararat, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...

Locations impacted include...
Stuart...
Francisco...
Ararat...
Critz...
Woodville...
Collinstown...
and Patrick Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
